history.text: Hello
Have you seen this movie?
I have seen it a couple of times!
I think I've seen it. There's so many Batman movies that I can't keep track
I didn't know Liam Neeson was in this movie! I really like him
Christopher Nolan is one of my favorite directors, so I had to see it! That is true but I think this is one of the better ones.
Liam is great in action movies.
I enjoy Christian Bale as Batman. He plays him well
Do you agree with the rating of this movie?
He did a great job getting into the character. Being really fit certainly helps.
Yes that's true, especially for a super-hero role
I think the reviews are fair, though I would rate it higher. what did you think?
Well I agree with the rating. It's fair but it wasn't the best super-hero movie
What did you think about the key scenes?
I like that Alfred raised Bruce after his parents were killed. It shows that he really cares about the family
I didn't remember that he got attacked by bats in a well and that's why he's afraid of them! Makes sense hahah
Thats true it felt genuine. How well do you think it captures the text of comic book vs bringing it to real life balance? *breaks 4th wall

I actually never read the comic books. I don't think I've actually ever read a comic book. But it's hard to not tell this story properly. Everyone knows Batman and I think the movie captured his essence very well
What do you think?
I agree, it felt referential to the comic books while still bringing the character to real life. What did you think of the critical reception?
I'm not to sure about the critical reception, and now that I'm reading the second key scene, I don't think I've actually seen this film hahaha
Ra's al guhl and carmine falcone are great examples of the writers pulling from the comic universe to build the universe. oh really? You should check it out!
Yeah those characters don't sound familiar to me at all
I do have to check it out
And you should also look into the comic books, or if you are into video games (the arkham series) it will help you appreciate this movie even more.
Yeah I think I will, so is the League of Shadows good or bad?
They are morally grey, they kill and murder anyone who gets in their way with their main mission being to kill all the bad guys but even good guys if they get in the way.
And am I reading the description correctly when it said Batman served time in prison? Or was that another character?
And of course Alfred comes to the rescue again! He's a good dude. One of my favorite characters
Yeah, he goes to a foreign country and gets arrested, it is there that he gets inducted into the league of shadows.

Is Crane one of the main villai
ns in this movie?
it seems there's always a corrupt doctor in these types of films
He is a minor villian in this film but he plays a role in the plot.
Yeah, batman is very much about the archetypes.
Well I think I need to watch this film. It got a good rating and the plot seems interesting
It is a great film and worth checking out.
